NAME
    pretty-typescript - Format TypeScript files using Prettier

SYNOPSIS
    pretty-typescript [ADDITIONAL_OPTIONS...]

DESCRIPTION
    The pretty-typescript function runs Prettier on TypeScript and TSX files
    in the current directory and its subdirectories. It applies specific
    formatting rules and allows for additional Prettier options to be passed.

OPTIONS
    ADDITIONAL_OPTIONS
        Any additional Prettier options can be passed as arguments to the function.

PRETTIER OPTIONS (preset)
    --write                 Modify files in-place
    --tab-width 4           Use 4 spaces for indentation
    --print-width 120       Set maximum line width to 120 characters
    --quote-props consistent Use consistent quoting for object properties
    --trailing-comma none   Remove trailing commas

EXAMPLES
    pretty-typescript
    pretty-typescript --single-quote

SEE ALSO
    prettier(1), npx(1)

NOTES
    This function requires Node.js, npx, and Prettier to be installed.
    Prettier can be installed via npm: npm install --save-dev prettier

Breakdown:

1. pretty-typescript () { ... }: Defines a function named pretty-typescript.

2. npx prettier: Runs Prettier using npx, which allows execution of npm package binaries.

3. --write "**/*.{ts,tsx}": Formats all .ts and .tsx files in the current directory and subdirectories.

4. Formatting options:
   - --tab-width 4: Sets indentation to 4 spaces
   - --print-width 120: Sets maximum line length to 120 characters
   - --quote-props consistent: Ensures consistent quoting of object properties
   - --trailing-comma none: Removes trailing commas

5. "$@": Allows passing additional Prettier options when calling the function.

This function provides a convenient way to format TypeScript files with predefined Prettier settings, while still allowing flexibility for additional options.
